The paper deals with network location problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and graph theory. The use of LP relaxations and approximation algorithms suggests that the paper belongs to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The focus on tree instances and the use of preprocessing techniques suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) which often deal with geometric and optimization problems. Finally, the use of approximation guarantees and integrality gaps suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
